On February 21, 2018, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to honor the memory of Reverend Billy Graham. The proclamation stated that on the day of his interment, the flag of the United States would be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset. The proclamation also directed that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same period at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.